\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. P. epihydrus} Rafin., {\i Med. Reposit.} ({\i New York}) Hexade 2, {\b 5}: 354 (1808). Rhizome creeping; stems compressed. Upper leaves up to 7 × 2·5 cm, floating, oblong to elliptical, cuneate at the base, opaque. Submerged leaves up to 8 mm wide, ribbon-like, rounded to subacute, 5- to 7-veined, the midrib with a broad border of lacunae extending sideways towards the inner lateral veins or sometimes beyond them. Stipules open. Carpels 4. Fruitlets 2·5-3·5 mm; embryo subspiral.{\i  N.W. Scotland, N.W. England.} Br. ({\i North America.})
\par

