\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 12. P. rutilus} Wolfg. in Schultes & Schultes fil., {\i Mantissa}{\b  3}: 362 (1827). Rhizome absent; winter-buds terminating lateral branches, strongly ribbed at the base, with fibrous sheaths. Leaves all submerged, up to 1·5 mm wide but usually less than 1 mm, rigid, gradually narrowed at the apex to a fine, almost bristle-like point (involucral leaves occasionally slightly dilated at the apex), 3(-5)-veined, the lateral veins conspicuous; nodal glands small, inconspicuous. Stipules closed, tubular towards the base at least when young, firm, strongly veined, fibrous-persistent. Carpels 4. Fruitlets 1·5-2 mm.{\i  N., C. & E. Europe, from N. Scotland and N.W. France eastwards to C. Ukraine and S.C. Russia; very local.} Br Da Fe Ga Ge Po ?Rm Rs (N, B, C, W)
