\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. P. trichoides} Cham. & Schlecht., {\i Linnaea}{\b  2}: 175 (1827). Rhizome absent; stems very slender, subterete; winter-buds terminating lateral branches. Leaves all submerged, up to 1·5 mm wide but usually less than 1 mm, gradually acute, 3-veined, the lateral veins very faint, the midrib prominent and usually much thickened especially towards the base; nodal glands small. Stipules open, convolute, herbaceous, shining-green. Carpels 1-3. Fruitlets 3 mm, the dorsal keel usually muriculate. 2n = 26.{\i  Most of Europe, northwards to Scotland, S. Sweden and C. Russia.} Au Be Br Bu Cr Cz Da Ga Ge Gr He Ho Hs Hu It Ju *Lu Po Rm Rs (B, C, W, E) Si Su.
