\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 17. P. compressus} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 127 (1753) ({\i P. zosterifolius} Schumacher). Rhizome absent; stems strongly compressed. Leaves all submerged, 2-4 mm wide, mucronate, appearing many-veined (5 vascular veins interspersed with very numerous, fine, vein-like sclerenchymatous strands), the midrib closely bordered by lacunae especially towards the base. Stipules open. Spikes many-flowered, cylindrical, usually shorter than the peduncle. Carpels usually 2. Fruitlets 3-4·5 mm. 2n = 26.{\i  N., C. & E. Europe, southwards to S.C. France and S. Ukraine; isolated records from Crna Gora and N. W. Greece.} Au Be Br Cz Da Fe Ga Ge Gr He Ho ?Hs Ju No Po Rm Rs (N, B, C, W, E) Su.
